A brief overview of main theories and hypoteses about how ecological factors affect the evolution of animal behaviour will be provided. The optimality models of behaviour, life history strategies, cooperation and conflict, altruism, optimal foraging theory, group living, territoriality, sexual conflict, mating systems, biocommunication, evolutionary "arms race" etc will be studied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To receive an introduction to basic principles of behavioural ecology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, a person possesses an elementary knowledge about the functions of various behavioural patterns, main problems, theories and hypotheses.
